#MEM id=references source=/root/yvon/agent-department/COO/diana/skills/marketplace/traction-eos/references/level-10.md savings=11%
M|Leve|tx|The Level 10 Meeting is the most important meeting in the Entrepreneurial Operating sy. It is a weekly, 90-minute leadership team meeting that follows a precise agenda, creates accountability, surfaces issues, and keeps the company on track. When run well, it eliminates the need for most other meetings. This guide covers every section of the agenda, facilitation protocols, rules, and how to consistently score 8 or higher.
M|Why |At t|if the meeting scores below 8, the team discusses what to improve, and the facilitator adjusts.
M|The |Befo|
M|The |tx|\| Rule \| Why It Matters \|
M|The |tx|\|------\|---------------\|
M|The |tx|\| Same day, same time, every week \| Rhythm creates discipline. No rescheduling. \|
M|The |tx|\| Starts on time \| Waiting for stragglers trains people to be late. Start w/o them. \|
M|The || En|work expands to fill the time available. Hard stop at 90 minutes. \|
M|The |tx|\| No cancellations \| The meeting happens even if two people are out. Cancel only for true emergencies (office fire, not a client call). \|
M|The |tx|\| Full attendance expected \| If someone misses more than 2 in a quarter, it is an issue to IDS. \|
M|The |tx|\| No phones or laptops \| Except for the person taking notes and anyone referencing the shared agenda. \|
M|The |tx|\| One conversation at a time \| Side conversations are stopped immediately by the facilitator. \|
M|The |tx|The agenda is fixed. It does not change week to week. This predictability is a feature, not a bug. Everyone knows exactly what to expect, which reduces meeting anxiety and increases preparation.
M|The |tx|```
M|The |00|00 - 05:00  Segue (Good News)
M|The |05|00 - 10:00  Scorecard rv
M|The |10|00 - 15:00  Rock rv
M|The |15|00 - 20:00  cs/Employee Headlines
M|The |20|00 - 25:00  To-Do List rv
M|The |25|00 - 85:00  IDS (Identify, Discuss, Solve)
M|The |85|00 - 90:00  Conclude
M|The |tx|```
M|Purp|tx|Start w/ a human connection. Each person shares one piece of good news -- personal or professional. This transitions the team from whatever they were doing before the meeting into a present, connected state.
M|Prot|it|Go around the table, one person at a time
M|Prot|it|30-45 seconds per person
M|Prot|it|Personal news is encouraged (not just work wins)
M|Prot|it|No discussion or follow-up questions during the segue
M|Prot|it|The facilitator keeps it moving
M|Exam|it|"My daughter scored her first soccer goal this weekend."
M|Exam|it|"We just signed a deal I've been working on for three months."
M|Exam|it|"I finished a half marathon on Saturday."
M|Exam|it|"Our team hit 100% on their to-dos for the first time."
M|Why |tx|The Segue sets the tone. Teams that skip it jump straight into problems and data w/o any human connection. The 5-minute investment builds trust and camaraderie that pays dividends during difficult IDS conversations later in the meeting.
M|Purp|tx|rv the weekly Scorecard to identify any metrics that are off track.
M|Prot|tx|1. Display the Scorecard (screen, projector, or printout)
M|Prot|tx|2. Go metric by metric. The owner states the number.
M|Prot|tx|3. If the number is on track (green), move on. No discussion.
M|Prot|4. I|"Off track. Dropping to Issues List."
M|Prot|tx|5. No discussion during Scorecard rv. All off-track numbers will be IDS'd later.
M|Prot|6. T|5 minutes maximum.
M|Faci|it|Move quickly. The Scorecard is a scan, not a deep dive.
M|Faci|- If|"We'll get to it during IDS."
M|Faci|it|Track consecutive red weeks. Three in a row means it automatically becomes the first issue in IDS.
M|Purp|tx|rv the status of every quarterly Rock to ensure progress is on track.
M|Prot|tx|1. Display the Rock sheet
M|Prot|2. G|"On track" or "Off track."
M|Prot|tx|3. No discussion or explanation during rv
M|Prot|tx|4. Off-track rocks are noted and may be added to the Issues List
M|Prot|5. T|5 minutes
M|On T|tx|A Rock is on track if the owner believes, based on current progress, it will be done by the end of the quarter. It is off track if there is meaningful risk of missing the deadline.
M|On T|**Ru|**
M|On T|it|Be honest. Declaring "on track" when you know it is at risk wastes the team's time when the truth surfaces later.
M|On T|it|Off track is not shameful. It is information that lets the team help.
M|On T|it|If a Rock has been off track for 3+ consecutive weeks, it must be IDS'd.
M|Purp|tx|Share brief, important updates abt cs and employees that the leadership team needs to know abt.
M|Prot|tx|1. Go around the table
M|Prot|tx|2. Each person shares 1-2 headlines (not stories, headlines)
M|Prot|3. F|"[Good/Bad news]: [One sentence summary]"
M|Prot|tx|4. If a hl needs discussion, it drops to the Issues List
M|Prot|5. T|5 minutes
M|Exam|tx|\| tp \| hl \|
M|Exam|tx|\|------\|----------\|
M|Exam|tx|\| cs (positive) \| "Acme Corp renewed for 3 years and doubled their contract" \|
M|Exam|tx|\| cs (negative) \| "Beta Industries is threatening to leave due to implementation delays" \|
M|Exam|tx|\| Employee (positive) \| "Sarah passed her certification exam on the first attempt" \|
M|Exam|tx|\| Employee (negative) \| "We lost two engineers to a cr this week" \|
M|Head|The |"That sounds important. Add it to the Issues List and we'll IDS it."
M|Purp|tx|rv every to-do from the previous week and confirm whether it is done or not done.
M|Prot|tx|1. Display the to-do list from last week
M|Prot|2. R|"Done" or "Not done."
M|Prot|tx|3. Done to-dos are checked off and removed
M|Prot|tx|4. Not-done to-dos are either carried forward (one more week) or dropped to the Issues List
M|Prot|5. T|5 minutes
M|To-D|tx|\| Rule \| Details \|
M|To-D|tx|\|------\|---------\|
M|To-D|tx|\| 7-day items only \| To-dos are done within one week \|
M|To-D|tx|\| 100% = done \| Partial completion is "not done" \|
M|To-D|tx|\| Each to-do has an owner \| One name, no shared ownership \|
M|To-D|| Ta|90%+ completion \| If the team consistently falls below 90%, it is an issue \|
M|To-D|tx|\| Carried forward once \| If a to-do is not done two weeks in a row, it goes to IDS \|
M|What|- "J|Send revised proposal to Acme Corp by Friday" (clear)
M|What|it|"Look into mk stuff" (too vague -- who? what? when?)
M|What|Ever|Who will do what by when?
M|Purp|tx|Identify, Discuss, and Solve the most important issues facing the organization. This is where the real work of the Level 10 meeting happens.
M|Prot|**St|bd the Issues List (2 minutes)**
M|Prot|- As|"Does anyone have new issues to add?"
M|Prot|it|Quickly capture new issues in 3-5 words each
M|Prot|**St|Prioritize (3 minutes)**
M|Prot|it|Read the full list aloud
M|Prot|- As|"What are the top 3 issues? Which three, if solved today, wld have the greatest impact?"
M|Prot|it|Number them 1, 2, 3
M|Prot|**St|IDS Issue #1**
M|Prot|- **|** The person who raised the issue states it clearly in one sentence. Ask: "What is the real issue here?" Dig to root cause.
M|Prot|- **|** Open the floor. Relevant perspectives are shared. Facilitator stops tangents.
M|Prot|- **|** The team decides. Action items are created w/ who/what/when. The issue is resolved or escalated.
M|Prot|**St|Repeat for remaining issues**
M|Prot|it|After each issue, re-prioritize remaining issues
M|Prot|it|Continue until the 60 minutes are up
M|Prot|it|Unsolved issues carry forward to nx week
M|Time|tx|\| Issue Complexity \| Typical Time \| Facilitator Action \|
M|Time|tx|\|-----------------\|-------------\|-------------------\|
M|Time|tx|\| Simple decision \| 5 minutes \| Drive quickly to a decision \|
M|Time|tx|\| Moderate discussion \| 10-15 minutes \| Allow input, then push for resolution \|
M|Time|tx|\| Complex st issue \| 15-20 minutes \| If not resolved in 20 minutes, cr a to-do to schedule a separate meeting \|
M|Time|tx|\| Recurring issue \| Varies \| Address why it keeps recurring, not just the symptom \|
M|The |The |
M|The |- **|"That's a separate issue. I'm adding it to the list."
M|The |- **|"I think we have enough input. What's the decision?"
M|The |- **|"We haven't heard from you on this. What's your take?"
M|The |it|**Break ties.** If the team cannot agree after sufficient discussion, the Integrator makes the call.
M|The |it|**Capture action items in real time.** Every solved issue produces a to-do (who, what, when) or a decision.
M|Purp|tx|Wrap up the meeting w/ clarity on nx steps and feedback on meeting qual.
M|Prot|**St|Recap To-Dos (2 minutes)**
M|Prot|tx|Read aloud every new to-do created during the meeting. Confirm each owner understands their commitment.
M|Prot|**St|Cascading Messages (1 minute)**
M|Prot|Ask|"Are there any decisions or messages from this meeting that need to be communicated to your teams?" List them. Ensure consistent messaging.
M|Prot|**St|Rate the Meeting (2 minutes)**
M|Prot|tx|Each person rates the meeting 1-10. Go around the table.
M|Prot|- If|"Great meeting. See you nx week."
M|Prot|- If|Ask that person: "What wld have made it an 8?" Take note for nx week.
M|Rati|tx|\| Rating \| Meaning \|
M|Rati|tx|\|--------\|---------\|
M|Rati|tx|\| 10 \| Best possible use of 90 minutes. All important issues addressed. Clear outcomes. \|
M|Rati|tx|\| 8-9 \| Productive meeting. Most issues addressed. Minor improvements possible. \|
M|Rati|tx|\| 6-7 \| Decent but felt unfocused or rushed. Key issues may have been skipped. \|
M|Rati|tx|\| 4-5 \| sig dysfunction. Too much tangent, not enough solving, or wrong issues prioritized. \|
M|Rati|tx|\| 1-3 \| Meeting failed. Waste of time. Fundamental problems w/ facilitation or participation. \|
M|The |Meet|
M|The |it|[ ] Scorecard numbers are updated
M|The |it|[ ] Rock statuses are current
M|The |it|[ ] To-dos from last week are done or flagged
M|The |it|[ ] Issues to raise are thought through (not raised cold)
M|The |tx|\| Technique \| Impact \|
M|The |tx|\|-----------\|--------\|
M|The |tx|\| Start on time, every time \| Sets the standard for discipline \|
M|The |tx|\| Enforce the agenda strictly \| Prevents scope creep and overruns \|
M|The |tx|\| Stop tangents immediately \| Keeps IDS focused and productive \|
M|The |tx|\| Push for decisions, not just discussion \| Creates momentum and resolution \|
M|The |tx|\| End on time, every time \| Builds trust that 90 minutes means 90 minutes \|
M|The |it|Every person speaks during IDS (facilitator draws out quiet members)
M|The |it|No one dominates (facilitator manages airtime)
M|The |it|People are honest abt off-track rocks and red Scorecard numbers
M|The |it|The team engages in healthy conflict, not avoidance
M|Comm|tx|\| Dysfunction \| Symptom \| Fix \|
M|Comm|tx|\|-------------\|---------\|-----\|
M|Comm|| **|"Good point, adding to the list. Back to the current issue." \|
M|Comm|| **|"Let's hear from everyone. Sarah, you first." \|
M|Comm|| **|"I sense there's an issue we're avoiding. What is it?" \|
M|Comm|tx|\| **Scorecard not updated** \| Numbers missing or stale \| Make it a to-do. If repeated, IDS it as a process issue. \|
M|Comm|| **|"What specifically wld improve this meeting?" \|
M|Comm|tx|\| **To-dos always incomplete** \| Same items carry forward week after week \| IDS the pattern. Is it capacity? Commitment? Accountability? \|
M|Comm|tx|\| **Rocks always on track until week 12** \| People hide bad news until the last minute \| cr safety for early off-track declarations. Praise honesty, not perfection. \|
M|Comm|tx|\| **Meeting keeps running over 90 min** \| Agenda discipline has broken down \| Hard stop at 90 minutes. Unsolved issues carry forward. No exceptions. \|
M|Comm|| **|"What do you think abt this?" \|
M|Comm|| **|"What structural change will prevent this from recurring?" \|
M|Leve|**Be|** Room booked, Scorecard updated, Rock statuses current, to-dos from last week reviewed, issues identified, agenda displayed.
M|Leve|**Du|** Segue (5 min), Scorecard (5 min), Rocks (5 min), Headlines (5 min), To-dos (5 min), IDS (60 min), Conclude w/ rating (5 min). New to-dos captured w/ who/what/when.
M|Leve|**Af|** To-do list distributed within 1 hour. Cascading messages to teams within 24 hours. Below-8 ratings addressed before nx meeting.